## üì± Application Workflow

The CropIQ mobile application follows a user-centric workflow designed to
provide real-time, location-aware crop recommendations.

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ User Registration & Login
- User registers using username, password, location, and preferred language
- Existing users can log in using stored credentials

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Location Permission
- App requests mandatory location access
- User‚Äôs geographical coordinates are used to identify the soil region

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Satellite View Initialization
- Google Maps is launched in **satellite view mode**
- The selected location is mapped to corresponding satellite imagery

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Soil Analysis
- Satellite image of the selected region is processed
- The trained **EfficientNet-B7 model** classifies the soil type

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Crop Recommendation
- Predicted soil type is matched with a soil‚Äìcrop recommendation dataset
- Suitable crops are identified based on soil compatibility

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Results Display
- Recommended crops are displayed in image and text format
- Model accuracy and confidence score are shown to the user

### 7Ô∏è‚É£ User Interaction & Updates
- User can refresh location or change region
- Updated recommendations are generated dynamically

